The following codes are a result of research undertaken during my PhD at the Universtiy of Cambridge. 


spincube.py: The spin density code helps plot spin densities along x y and z spin axes. It generates the cube files asociated with each spin density direction.  It only needs the coefficients/density matrix supplied to it.

coefficients.py: Generates the fock matrix using coefficients, one and two electron integral matrices. 



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%%%%%%%%%%%%%% MixedSpinVisualisationSoftware %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

The directory 'mixedspin' contains python files that will generate a colour wheel mapping of spin density (for occupied MOs) (spindensity_occupiedMOs) and rotate your spin vectors in the lowest occupied molecular orbital along the z-direction (alignspinaxislowocc). It is specifically designed to visualise non-collinear spin in real-GHF systems. The following file also requires installation of Quantel, a software package developed by Dr Hugh Burton. 
The python files are built for a real GHF calculation on an H3 ring. 
